    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "By default, pandas aligns the right series on the columns (axis 1) of the left dataframe. \r\nSo if you try to do `shape(150000, 2) - shape(150000,)`, you get `shape(150000, 150000)`, hence the memory error.\r\n\r\nIf you want to specify the alignment, you can use the equivalent methods (instead of operator):\r\n\r\n```\r\nIn [20]: df.sub(df.mean(axis=1), axis=0)\r\nOut[20]: \r\n               0         1\r\n0       0.020379 -0.020379\r\n1       0.103582 -0.103582\r\n2      -0.035321  0.035321\r\n3       0.164272 -0.164272\r\n...\r\n```\r\n"
  },
